<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-22T18:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-22T18:16:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4000</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-22T19:00:00-04:16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>My April 15, 11 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d351fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_255">p.
                                    255</ref>.</note> The Government newspaper to-night says that
                                Argentine Government sent peremptory instructions to the Minister,
                                Berlin, to demand apology for sinking brigantine besides money
                                indemnity, and anticipating Germany’s [refusal?] says that
                                Argentina’s course is clear.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SFJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>